[gd_resource type="Resource" script_class="HandbookPage" load_steps=2 format=3]

[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://resources/HandbookPage.gd" id="1_page"]

[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_page")
page_id = "siem"
title = "SIEM FORENSIC ANALYSIS"
content = "[b][color=#006CFF]DIGITAL CCTV[/color][/b]
The SIEM records every 'event' on our network. Think of logs as footprints in the digital snow. If an attacker moves, they leave a record here.

[b]HOW TO INVESTIGATE:[/b]
1. [b]Search[/b]: Use IPs or keywords found in emails to filter the noise.
2. [b]Analyze[/b]: Check the 'Forensic Report' panel for technical details.
3. [b]Document[/b]: Drag and drop relevant logs onto the Ticket Queue to build your case.

[b]VOLUME GRAPHS:[/b]
The graph at the top shows traffic spikes. A sudden vertical wall usually means a [b]DDoS Attack[/b] or a large [b]Data Breach[/b] has started."
